## 2026-03-28 - Context-aware token surfacing
- Implemented context-aware token suggestions in the Selection Inspector. When a Figma layer is selected, the plugin now surfaces 5-8 most relevant tokens based on type matching, value similarity, sibling usage, and existing bindings — shown in a collapsible "Suggested" section above the property groups.
- Added `rankTokensForSelection()` scoring function that aggregates `scoreBindCandidate` scores across all eligible properties, with bonus scoring for already-bound tokens and a minimum threshold of 15 to filter irrelevant results.
- Created `SuggestedTokens.tsx` component with color swatches, token paths, match reason labels, property labels, and hover-reveal Apply buttons.

